    "causal_summary": "Bridges the natural-language → code-identifier gap by expanding queries with camelCase / snake_case / PascalCase / kebab-case splits, common code-domain synonyms (walker/finder, util/helper, parser/lexer), and a configurable user-synonym dictionary. Runs BEFORE embedding so dense + FTS5 both benefit. Embedder-agnostic, reranker-agnostic, future-proof for any future identifier convention. Targets the 'natural language asks, but corpus stores identifiers' failure mode evidenced in 011 phase-2 bench probes 1, 5, 12, 15.",
